  ## Description
  
  ```
  Learn more about our QuickBooks Services:  https://www.fourlane.com/quickbooks-consulting/
  View upcoming webinars and events:  https://www.fourlane.com/events/
  
  Talk to the QuickBooks Enterprise experts at Fourlane today. Get the best pricing, tailored demo and QuickBooks consulting services.
  
  QuickBooks Online Advanced supports more users, has more advanced reports, and includes premium support. Pay annually and save 50% off. 
  
  Call brief
  Lori from Fourlane discussed the importance of proper inventory management using QuickBooks, highlighting features such as the Inventory Center, Site Operations, Landed Cost tracking, and Cycle Counting to maintain accurate inventory levels and financial reporting. She emphasized the need for a solid base-level inventory workflow before implementing advanced features, and recommended regular cycle counts to identify and address any process issues, ultimately helping the company better manage its inventory and ensure the accuracy of its financial data.
  
  Key points
  1. Inventory management is crucial, and QuickBooks has various features to help manage it, such as inventory parts, multiple inventory sites, bin locations, and landed cost.
  2. Negative inventory should be avoided, and Fourlane recommends running the Negative Inventory Listing report daily to identify and resolve any issues.
  3. The Inventory Stock Status report is valuable for monitoring inventory levels and triggering purchase orders.
  4. Cycle counts are important for verifying inventory accuracy and preparing for year-end physical inventory.
  5. Fourlane emphasizes the importance of having a well-designed inventory management workflow to ensure data integrity.
  6. Fourlane is available to provide further assistance and guidance on improving inventory management processes.
  
  Visit https://www.fourlane.com, call us at 1.800.931.2120, or email us at info@fourlane.com today. 
  
